The Federal Road Safety Corp, Zone 12 comprising of Bauchi, Borno and Yobe states, on Saturday, embarked on a walk exercise as part of activities lined up to celebrate the 34 years of the establishment of the Corp. The Zonal Commander, FRSC, Rotimi Adeleye, and the Sector Commander, Bauchi State, Yusuf Abdullahi, led other top officers of the Zone and the Command to the road walk which began at the Zonal Headquarters along Dass Road. They walked to the Jos Road motor park where he (Adeleye) addressed the officials of the road transport union, drivers and passengers. They, thereafter, returned to their take-off point. The about six kilometres road walk exercise began at 7.00am and ended at about 9.20am. Here are the pictures:  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com